{
  "texts": [
    "We also made a novel discovery in that a prediagnosis from a wearable increases the likelihood for anticoagulant prescription and an eventual AF diagnosis.",
    "At the index diagnosis, the existence of a prediagnosis from a wearable did not distinguish patients based on clinical characteristics but did correlate with anticoagulant prescription.Our work establishes the feasibility and efficacy of an EHR-based surveillance system for consumer wearable devices.",
    "Further work is necessary to generalize these findings for patient populations at other sites.",
    "Din, Nigam H Shah.",
    "Originally published in JMIR Medical Informatics (https://medinform.jmir.org), 04.04.2024."
  ]
}